## GAP 2: Node HandlerFunc Missing `noop_handler` / NoOpHandlerFunc

### Go Code: /tmp/tork-go/middleware/node/node.go
```go
type HandlerFunc func(context.Context, *tork.Node) error

type MiddlewareFunc func(next HandlerFunc) HandlerFunc

func ApplyMiddleware(h HandlerFunc, mws []MiddlewareFunc) HandlerFunc {
    return func(ctx context.Context, n *tork.Node) error {
        nx := next(ctx, 0, mws, h)
        return nx(ctx, n)
    }
}
```
No explicit `NoOpHandlerFunc` defined, but the pattern exists.

### Rust Code: /home/lewis/src/twerk/middleware/node/mod.rs (lines 9, 57-59)
```rust
pub type HandlerFunc = Arc<dyn Fn(Arc<Context>, &Node) -> Result<(), NodeError> + Send + Sync>;

pub fn noop_handler() -> HandlerFunc {
    Arc::new(|_ctx: Arc<Context>, _node: &Node| Ok(()))
}
```
Rust has `noop_handler()` which Go does NOT have - this is Rust-only functionality.

### Expected Fix:
This gap is Rust-ADDING functionality that Go doesn't have. No change needed unless Go parity requires removing this.

