## GAP 8: Job Webhook Event Matching - Default Event Handling

### Go Code: /tmp/tork-go/middleware/job/webhook.go (lines 24, 27)
```go
if wh.Event != webhook.EventJobStateChange && wh.Event != webhook.EventDefault && wh.Event != webhook.EventJobProgress {
    continue
}
if et == StateChange && wh.Event != webhook.EventJobStateChange && wh.Event != webhook.EventDefault {
    continue
}
```
Default event matches StateChange only.

### Rust Code: /home/lewis/src/twerk/middleware/job/webhook.rs (lines 85-105)
```rust
fn should_fire_webhook(et: EventType, wh: &Webhook) -> bool {
    let event = wh.event.as_deref().unwrap_or(EVENT_DEFAULT);
    match et {
        EventType::StateChange => {
            event.is_empty() || event == EVENT_JOB_STATE_CHANGE || event == EVENT_DEFAULT
        }
        EventType::Progress => event.is_empty() || event == EVENT_JOB_PROGRESS,
        _ => false,
    }
}
```
Default/empty event matches BOTH StateChange AND Progress in Rust, but Go only matches StateChange.

### Expected Fix:
Change Rust logic so empty/default event only matches StateChange:
```rust
EventType::StateChange => {
    event.is_empty() && wh.event.is_none() || event == EVENT_JOB_STATE_CHANGE
}
// For Progress, empty should NOT match:
EventType::Progress => event == EVENT_JOB_PROGRESS,
```

